headline: INVNT® Reports Record Growth, Expanding Global Infrastructure and Capabilities Across All Regions
summary: NEW YORK, February 16, 2026--INVNT® reports 60% year over year growth in 2025, expanding global infrastructure, AI innovation, and client partnerships worldwide.

headline: Will Tariffs Remain a Major Headwind for General Motors in 2026?
summary: GM incurs $3.1B in 2025 tariff costs and offsets more than 40% of the hit. It expects $3B-$4B in tariff headwinds this year.

headline: General Motors Taps Lucid Veteran To Steer EV And Software Shift
summary: General Motors (NYSE:GM) is accelerating plans for its next generation EV and software platforms. The company has appointed former Lucid executive Claudia Gast to lead strategy, corporate development, and technology partnerships. The move signals a renewed focus on EV technology, software architecture, and autonomous driving capabilities. For you as an investor, this update sits at the intersection of where autos and tech are increasingly overlapping. GM still generates much of its business...

headline: 2 Value Stocks with Exciting Potential and 1 Facing Challenges
summary: Value stocks typically trade at discounts to the broader market, offering patient investors the opportunity to buy businesses when they’re out of favor. The key risk, however, is that these stocks are usually cheap for a reason – five cents for a piece of fruit may seem like a great deal until you find out it’s rotten.
